version_description: Existing versions have wrong chords in the verses (most notably they all have Em when it is actually a major chord) and chorus. No full arrangement of the fast versions. Added a tab of the riff, too.
In my version I've put chords which cover intro, solo and end
Complete and complex chords play on acoustic guitar or Electric guitar with Chorus,Delay and Reverb effects https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Jtpf8N5IDE.

This version is for a baritone/low tenor. If you would like to transpose it to the original, go up to the key of C Minor. Older versions of this chart don't transpose well, so this is a needed facelift. The diminished chords in this song can be done in any position because they're fully diminished and all the root notes of a fully diminished chord are interchangeable. Depending on where you choose to play this on the neck you could use many different variations of said diminished chords.
This is another one I do live acoustically. Dm/A xx3231 Dm7 xx0221 and on the final B C use bar chords to get the higher notes.
